Description: Fifteen papyrus fragments. Five fragments are very large and bear multiple lines of Coptic text on both sides, written along the fibres on one side and against them on the other. Seven very small fragments bear traces of text on one or both sides. A further three very small fragments are blank on both sides. The fragments are understood to be numbered in columns (top to bottom, left to right) as seen from the scanned image labelled as 'front'.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380793) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380793)
